This paper discusses security and privacy issues in smart grids, which are related to cryptography and distributed systems. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The paper also discusses data aggregation and access control, which are related to distributed computing and systems, making cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) and cs.SY (Systems and Control) likely categories as well. Additionally, the paper discusses the use of homomorphic encryption and attribute-based encryption, which are specific cryptographic techniques, making cs.SE (Software Engineering) a possible category. Finally, the paper discusses the security architecture of smart grids, which is related to cyber-physical systems, making cs.CY (Computers and Society) a possible category as well.
